(22, NULL, 5, 4, '2', 'Bali Zoo - Night at The Zoo', NULL, NULL, 0, 100, '[{\"photo\":\"https:\\/\\/porttie.com\\/storage\\/images\\/2020\\/01\\/16\\/03b0f85ef3a119d291dae1ce4a23a94c.jpg\",\"type\":\"image\"}]', '<p>Bali Zoo invites you to experience nocturnal animals watching in their prime hour. The night at the zoo program begins at 6 pm and ends at 9 pm. It is a nice activity for adults and families with young kids while on holiday in Bali.</p><p>Guests are expected to arrive at the ticketing counter at least 5.30 pm. The night at the zoo package includes a la carte dinner that is proudly served at Wana Restaurant. through dinner menu that varied from barbeque to Indian vegetarian cuisine. While Churrascostyle international buffet is served for a group of 20 people or more.</p><p>Your night safari journey starts at Deer Park located right after the ticket counter. At the Deer Park, you are allowed to hand-feed those beautiful herbivores with veggies provided at the venue. Afterward, you will stop by at Wana Plaza. Here you will be served with a welcome drink and a great selection of finger foods. At this venue, you will have a chance to meet up and interact with an owl, phyton, armadillo and other animals available in the evening. Moreover, you can find out the lions\' diet and how the keepers feed them! You are also welcome to use this opportunity to help the keeper feeding the king of the jungle. Work alongside the keeper pulling the rope that transports the fresh meat into the enclosure.</p><p>Guests are invited to have dinner at Wana Restaurant by 7 pm before embarking on an adventurous night. Dining at Wana Restaurant is not just another evening; it is dinner next to the lions. Following the dinner is a fascinating tour around the zoo by torchlight. Our wonderful and knowledgeable guides will take you to an adventure in the zoo.</p><p>The nightlife in the zoo is wonderful and mysterious at the same time. It is hard to tell the difference between a sleeping bearcat or an active one watching us with its widen pupils; if the owl is being calm or keeping an eye to a prey. Also sometimes it is hard to spot the animals as they blend in with the environment. Our expert guide will help you to unravel the mystery and spot the animals.</p><p>Some night creatures, such as owls and large cats have evolved sight allows them to see easily in the dark, some have a good sense of smell, such as snakes, while some others have a special hearing ability. No wonder their behavior is so unique. A set of house rules, which are no flash photography, be calm, and not walking separately with the group are meant to be followed to keep the animals calm and make your night at the zoo the best ever.</p><p>Our guides are very informative. But you can always find out more information about the animals from the written information on display!</p><p>Your night at the zoo is ultimately wrapped with a night safari show featuring a group of talented fire dancers.</p><p><strong>Things to Pack in Your Carry-On :</strong></p><p>1. Insect repellent.</p><p>2. Camera, but remember to switch off the flash.</p><p>3. Hand sanitizer. We also provide hand sanitizer. Ourguides will distribute hand sanitizer before and after animal feeding,</p><p>and every time after animals encounter.</p><p><strong>Activity Program Inclusions:</strong></p><ol><li>Hotel return transfers service</li><li>Entry to the zoo</li><li>Welcome drinks and canapes</li><li>Deer feeding</li><li>Elephants feeding</li><li>Guided tour in the zoo</li><li>Nocturnal creatures encounters</li><li>A la carte dinner at Wana Restaurant</li><li>Fire dance performance</li><li>Insurance.</li></ol><p><strong><u>TERM AND CONDITIONS:</u></strong></p><p>1. Operation Hours & General Info:</p><ol><li><span style=\"color: rgb(244, 149, 57);\">Opening Hours :</span><span style=\"color: black;\">18:00:00 - 21:00:00 </span>except on Nyepi Day(silence day)</li><li>Children 2  12 years old, infant under 2 years old is free</li><li>Shows and schedule is subject to change without prior notice due weather conditions</li></ol><p>2. Cancelation policy:</p><p>Reservation cancelled less than 24 hours prior to arrival are charged 60% from rate</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 300, NULL, 300000.00, NULL, NULL, 'IDR', 0x00000000010100000007e863e366d15c4058d7b2c6ea3021c0, -8.59554120, 115.27190480, NULL, 'Sukawati', NULL, 'ID', NULL, '{\"age\":[\"Adult\",\"Child\"]}', NULL, '[{\"day\":1,\"start_time\":\"18:00\",\"end_time\":\"19:00\"},{\"day\":1,\"start_time\":\"19:00\",\"end_time\":\"20:00\"},{\"day\":1,\"start_time\":\"20:00\",\"end_time\":\"21:00\"},{\"day\":1,\"start_time\":\"21:00\",\"end_time\":\"22:00\"},{\"day\":2,\"start_time\":\"18:00\",\"end_time\":\"19:00\"},{\"day\":2,\"start_time\":\"19:00\",\"end_time\":\"20:00\"},{\"day\":2,\"start_time\":\"20:00\",\"end_time\":\"21:00\"},{\"day\":2,\"start_time\":\"21:00\",\"end_time\":\"22:00\"},{\"day\":3,\"start_time\":\"18:00\",\"end_time\":\"19:00\"},{\"day\":3,\"start_time\":\"19:00\",\"end_time\":\"20:00\"},{\"day\":3,\"start_time\":\"20:00\",\"end_time\":\"21:00\"},{\"day\":3,\"start_time\":\"21:00\",\"end_time\":\"22:00\"},{\"day\":4,\"start_time\":\"18:00\",\"end_time\":\"19:00\"},{\"day\":4,\"start_time\":\"19:00\",\"end_time\":\"20:00\"},{\"day\":4,\"start_time\":\"20:00\",\"end_time\":\"21:00\"},{\"day\":4,\"start_time\":\"21:00\",\"end_time\":\"22:00\"},{\"day\":5,\"start_time\":\"18:00\",\"end_time\":\"19:00\"},{\"day\":5,\"start_time\":\"19:00\",\"end_time\":\"20:00\"},{\"day\":5,\"start_time\":\"20:00\",\"end_time\":\"21:00\"},{\"day\":5,\"start_time\":\"21:00\",\"end_time\":\"22:00\"},{\"day\":6,\"start_time\":\"18:00\",\"end_time\":\"19:00\"},{\"day\":6,\"start_time\":\"19:00\",\"end_time\":\"20:00\"},{\"day\":6,\"start_time\":\"20:00\",\"end_time\":\"21:00\"},{\"day\":6,\"start_time\":\"21:00\",\"end_time\":\"22:00\"},{\"day\":7,\"start_time\":\"18:00\",\"end_time\":\"19:00\"},{\"da